The paper deals with interference management in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of relays, which is a common technique in wireless communication systems and falls under the signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper provides a comprehensive analysis of the performance measures, which involves mathematical modeling and analysis, making it relevant to the computer engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
